Description: Flight into Egypt, with Virgin and Child on donkey led by Joseph, in oval. c.1611/15 Engraving
Curator's comments: Not described in IFF, but mentioned in Le Blanc (cat. No.10) as an illustration for 'Heures du Roy Loys XIII' (Paris, Eustache Foucault, 1615) . However, it is pointed out in IFF that some of the plates listed in Le Blanc as illustrations to 'Heures...' (cat. Nos. 4-10) are likely to belong to 'L'Office de la Vierge Marie' (Paris, Eustache Foucauld, 1611/12) instead.
Bibliographic references: Le Blanc 1854-89 / Manuel de l'Amateur d'Estampes 1550-1820 (10)
Associated titles: Associated Title: Office de la Vierge Marie (1611-12 ?)
Associated Title: Heures du Roy Loys XIII (1615 ?)
